{"questionId":"32316173","questionHtml":"<p>Find <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>A</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>r</mi></mrow></mfrac></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>A</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>r</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mi>r</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1200</mn><msup><mi>r</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></math><em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>A1</strong><strong>(M1)(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note</strong>: Award <em><strong>A1</strong></em> for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mi>r</mi></math> seen, and <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em> for expressing <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1200</mn><mi>r</mi></mfrac></math> as <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1200</mn><msup><mi>r</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math> (can be implied through <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>∓</mo><mfrac><mn>1200</mn><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mfrac></math> seen), <em><strong>A1</strong></em> for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>1200</mn><msup><mi>r</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></math>. Award at most <em><strong>A1(M1)A0</strong></em> if any additional terms are seen.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"32316173","referenceCode":"24N.2.AHL.TZ0.2ei","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Find dAdr.","paper":"2","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"i","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 5—Calculus","Topic 5—Calculus","SL 5.5—Integration introduction, areas between curve and x axis"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}